                            <musicNotation>
                                <p>The hymns are notated with incipits in black square notation on a four-line red staff.</p>
                            </musicNotation>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text and musical notes in brown-black ink. Capitals in red. Some capitals touched with light brown ink. Rubrics in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/> Plain initial O over 3 lines, in red with interior reserved shapes, within a flourished blue frame.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="40v" scheme="folios"/> Plain initials in red ink over 1-3 lines throughout the volume.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="images">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/> Bas-de-page decoration. Man of Sorrows: Christ rising from the tomb, with a brown cross behind him. The scene is encircled by a green oval laurel wreath, placed in a mounted golden decoration of scrolls. Red and blue flowers and dots in the scrolls. The same kind of mounted decoration, but smaller and less elaborate, is placed in the lower margin of <locus from="40v" to="40v" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
